==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manitu
<hw>Man"i*tu</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A name given
by tribes of American Indians to a great spirit, whether good or evil,
or to any object of worship.</def> <rj><au>Tylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gitche <qex>Manito</qex> the mighty,⟦br⟧
The Great Spirit, the creator,⟦br⟧
Smiled upon his helpless children!</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Mitche <qex>Manito</qex> the mighty,⟦br⟧
He the dreadful Spirit of Evil,⟦br⟧
As a serpent was depicted.</q> <rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manitrunk</ent>⟦br⟧
